422-420 West 127th Street, south side, east of Lawrence Street. No. 420 is a three-story frame house with a brick wall up to the first story. No. 422 has a one-story frame shack in the front with a two-story house connecting in the rear. 1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York. Negative No. 369.

The same view at a later date. Note the 1-story frame house at No. 422 replaced with one of brick. June 21, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
